OL,3,CDid Keir Starmer need to ditch his
OL,4,C#28bn pledge?
OL,6,FHis hope is this would neutralise
OL,7,Fcharge that Labour's investment plan
OL,8,Fwould lead to higher taxes or higher
OL,9,Finterest rates.JBut the question is
OL,10,Fwhether he is thereby turning that
OL,11,Fmanifesto into a dud, a blank, a great
OL,12,Ffat yawnathon, for a UK that is crying
OL,13,Fout for big ideas and hope.JThere are
OL,14,Fa few important and related points to
OL,15,Fmake about this significant U-turn.
OL,16,FThe first is that for any economically
OL,17,Fliterate person, the #28 billion was
OL,18,Fno longer the lethal weapon for the
OL,19,FTories that they wanted it to be -
OL,20,Fafter said on my programme (and every
OL,21,Ftime she opens her mouth, anywhere)
OL,22,Fthat it would only be spent if it
OL,23,Fdidn't risk breaching the fiscal rules
OL,24,F(namely that debt as a share of
OL,25,Fnational income must be falling on a
OL,26,Frolling timetable of five years).JThis
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/7
