OL,6,FSo in that sense, the investment is no
OL,7,Fmore likely to increase inflation,
OL,8,Finterest rates or any other factor
OL,9,Faffecting our living standards than
OL,10,Fany spending or investment decision he
OL,11,Fmakes.JTo put it another way, the #28
OL,12,Fbillion had become, at the point that
OL,13,FReeves said the fiscal rules always
OL,14,Ftake precedent, simply a symbol of how
OL,15,FLabour's fiscal choices are different
OL,16,Ffrom those of the Tories.JThe #28
OL,17,Fbillion was a shorthand for "if there
OL,18,Fis money to invest, it will go on
OL,19,Finsulating homes, building giga
OL,20,Ffactories, connecting windfarms to the
OL,21,Fgrid and so on" and in the process
OL,22,Freduce household energy bills, create
OL,23,Fjobs, and keep the UK on track to meet
OL,24,Fits climate change pledges.JFor any
OL,25,Fleft-of-centre party, these are
OL,26,Frespectable - some would say noble -
