OL,3,CDid Keir Starmer need to ditch his
OL,4,C#28bn pledge?
OL,6,FStarmer will claim that Labour would
OL,7,Fstill prioritise more green investment
OL,8,Fthan the Tories. But his claims will
OL,9,Fsound less compelling, less exciting,
OL,10,Fless brave.JPerhaps what is most
OL,11,Fsurprising is that he has been
OL,12,Fallowing the government to set the
OL,13,Feconomic agenda - despite the Tories
OL,14,Fastonishing lack of popular support -
OL,15,Fby repeatedly saying he agrees the tax
OL,16,Fburden is too high, and that he would
OL,17,Fnot increase corporation tax, income
OL,18,Ftaxes and so on.JHe's defining Labour
OL,19,Fat the moment by what it would not do
OL,20,Fin government: he won't put up taxes,
OL,21,Fhe won't re-integrate the UK's economy
OL,22,Fwith that of the European Union (EU),
OL,23,Fhe won't restore the cap on bankers'
OL,24,Fbonuses, he may not abolish the House
OL,25,Fof Lords.JThat may limit the scope for
OL,26,Fthe Tories and their media supporters
